# Always run the code

**Always run the code.**

After changing code, scripts, or config that affect build/test/visualization:

- Run the relevant command yourself (e.g. tests, `main.py`, pandoc, pdflatex, `--visualize --figure N`).
- Do not only suggest the command or say "you can run X" — execute it in the terminal.
- Regenerate outputs (figures, PDF, etc.) when the code that produces them has changed.

If a command fails, fix the issue and rerun; do not leave execution to the user unless they explicitly ask to run it themselves.
